##############################################################################
## This subdirectory contains an extremely simple HTTP Client and Server.
##
## HttpClient (command) uses CURL, so it's pretty robust.
##
## HttpListen accepts connections on port 8080, creating a Server (defined in
##    HttpServer.*) for each accepted Socket. There's minimal error recovery.
##
## The Server is a self-starting and self-deleting Thread. It reads from the
##    accepted Socket (but ignores the data), then writes an HTTP/1.1 OK
##    message. Error recovery is almost non-existent.
##
